Description: web reconnaissance tool for authorized penetration testing
 ShadowMap is a web reconnaissance tool aimed at penetration testers
 and bug bounty researchers. It performs passive and active subdomain
 enumeration, DNS zone transfer attempts, port and service scanning,
 technology fingerprinting, and checks for common misconfigurations
 such as exposed .git directories, .env files, and backup archives.
 .
 Results can be exported as an HTML report or machine-readable JSON.
 A stealth mode is available to rotate user-agents and add delays
 for less intrusive scanning.
 .
 For authorized security testing only. Always obtain written
 permission before scanning a target you do not own.
